The paper deals with a model of probabilistic higher order computation based on cones and totally monotone functions, which has connections to linear logic and extends the earlier model of probabilistic coherence spaces. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given the focus on linear structures and the use of special adjoint functor theorem to define the tensor product, cs.LO and cs.IT seem to be the most likely sub-categories.
